CNCP v1 23179
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12254: `@vue-ignore` before defineProps generic params breaks compilation",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:54.662381+00:00",
  "text": "`@vue-ignore` before defineProps generic params breaks compilation\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.12\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nsee the render result\n\n### What is expected?\n\n`@vue-ignore` before defineProps generic params can work\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n`defineProps</* @vue-ignore */ A & B>()` breaks boolean casting in interface B\r\n`defineProps<A & /* @vue-ignore */ B>()` works well\r\n`defineProps<& /* @vue-ignore */ A & B>()` works well, but some rules in the VSCode may format it that will remove the first `&`\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: sfc",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
